This week has been good so far, and I know the rest of it will be too. Monday I went over to Derek's house and helped his mom with the kids. After Derek got home we hung out for a bit, then he took me to Pat's Pizza for dinner. Once we were done there he dropped me off at dance class. Let's see, yesterday I had a make-up dance lesson, which was ok. Um, this morning Derek's mom called and asked if I would come over and help her today because she wasn't feeling good at all. I went over to Reny's after mum came and got me, and I talked to the manager about my aplication, he said he was going to look over all the aplications next week because they're going to be hiring a bunch of people for five weeks because of the holiday season and all of that. So hopefully he'll hire me. I've turned in aplications to Burger King, Wendy's, but neither of them have gotten back to me yet. I've filled one out for J and B atlantic and the Grasshopper shop, and I have to go back to the Riverside Cafe and the John Edwards store to get their aplications because when I asked them they didn't have any at the time. So I've been doing alot of that lately. I've thought about asking the florist and Ruth Fosters, it wouldn't be too hard working with baby stuff, hehe. I've been doing so many things lately, I've just started a little Christmas decorating around the house, helping Derek's mom with the kids, job hunting, dance class two nights a week, and now I have to write up a book report for the book that I read a little bit ago. It might not seem like a lot to some people, but I feel pretty busy. Tomorrow I help Nola with the kids again and I have dance class, that will be the third time I've had dance this week, I'm already getting kind of sore from the last two. Anyway, I think I've typed enough for now. Latas y'all.

I waste daylight....I sleep in and I don't get out of bed until 11:3O-ish. Dance class last night was fun. I came in a few minutes late because I couldn't find my ballet shoes. When I got there I told my dance teacher I was late because I couldn't find them. And she said that she thought I had left them there after my last lesson....and they were. I think I should start stretching every night for at least a half hour..cuz I need to be flexible if I want to do ballet without hurting. Something else that's cool is this thing we're doing in tap.....we have to do flaps across the room in a "jogging" style, and it's supposed to sound a little like a horse troting, and last night I was actually doing it! The last time I was having trouble with it. A flap is a move where you only use the taps that are on your toes..you don't use your heel taps at all. Things with me and Derek are awesomely super. I talked to him last night, I like to hear his voice......I love him. Aaaaany way, I gotta call Burger King about a jobby..talk later peeps.
